There is a remarkable sostening of the preposition ad into ar, of which we have a few examples: thus ARFVISE, ARF(uerunl), ARVORSVM, all in 10, and ARVORSARIO three times in 12.

Generally speaking, therefore, in printing the text of Plautus it will be safe to retain the prepositions in composition unchanged, except in such cases as accipio, where our authorities are all opposed to the harder form.
